The damage bill is more than $400,000 and its cause is being investigated, A MFB statement said.

The site of Donovans was one of three original bathing houses built in 1920 on the St Kilda foreshore.

A passer-by reportedly spotted smoke coming from the restaurant's roof and alerted staff.

