Ms Donovan promised to rebuild her business and added: 'We love it and adore it, and hopefully the damage will all just be internal.'

MFB Commander Bruce Pickthall told 3AW radio: 'They're prepared to make Donovan's bigger and better than it was and thankfully St Kilda has still got one of its iconic buildings.

'It will come back. It will be trading in no time.'

The fire at Donovans comes after the iconic Stokehouse restaurant, on St Kilda beach, was also destroyed by a fire in January this year.

Around 200 customers were forced to flee and more than 70 firefighters battled for three hours to control the blaze.

